6. A6-northstar-proof-mapping: Produce the final completion note that maps each of the 7 North Star Required Proof items to the exact test file, quality script, document, or fixture that proves it. For each proof item: (1) SDK/schema/docs/UI agreement on trusted-code model → which tests/scripts/documents converge; (2) regression gate fails on sandboxing/runtime-permission/marketplace/third-party claims → which gate + fixture; (3) shader/ref readiness from graph-projected facts → which tests + gate prove graph authority; (4) fixture proving legacy-only fields not authoritative after projection disabled → which test; (5) user-facing export blocks from planner blockers → which tests trace the chain; (6) generated-module/provider/output-format/contribution/shader/live-binding blockers represented in planner → which test cases cover each blocker category; (7) quality checks pass from clean checkout → which aggregate command + baseline. This is explicitly requested as a deliverable; the task says 'Produce a final completion note that maps North Star proof requirements to concrete files/tests.'

