- UNMAPPED PATHS ARE CLEAN: renderRouter.ts calls planRender() and passes compositionGraph through plannerInput but contains zero direct legacy shader reads — no clip.app?.shader, config.app?.shaderPostprocess, TimelineShaderMetadata, or legacyTimelineShaderMetadata patterns. It relies entirely on planner authority.
- useRenderState.ts CLEAN: useRenderState.ts calls exportGuard.scanExportConfig() and planRender() (via planFromExportGuardResult) but has no direct forbidden legacy field reads. It imports hasTimelineShaderMetadata from exportGuard (an allow-listed file per the gate's EXPLICIT_OUT_OF_SCOPE_ALLOWLIST does not cover it, but the function's body lives in exportGuard.ts which IS monitored).
- routeScopeValidation.ts CLEAN: Pure utility for validating render route scopes against canonical RENDER_ROUTES. Contains no legacy shader field reads.
- renderability.ts CLEAN: Pure re-export barrel from SDK rendering modules. No legacy reads.
- NORTH STAR FIXTURE MISSING: The required proof — 'A fixture proves legacy-only shader/ref fields do not count as authoritative after projection is disabled' (NORTHSTAR.md line 28, M2 brief line 19) — does NOT exist in compositionGraphProjector.test.ts (1835 lines). The closest test at line 281 ('projects legacy clip and postprocess shader summaries into consumes edges') tests the HAPPY path where projection WORKS (legacy fields ARE projected), not the negative case where projection is disabled and legacy fields fail as authority.
- PARTIAL FIXTURE IN shaderValidation.test.ts: The test at line 388 ('validates shader composition from graph edges in graph order and ignores legacy stack authority') proves graph edges override a legacy-provided shader stack, but this tests shader stack collision resolution (one-shader-per-scope), NOT that legacy-only fields lose authority when CompositionGraph projection is disabled at the planner level.
- RENDERPLANNER LEGACY BLOCKER EXISTS: renderPlanner.ts function legacyGraphCompatibilityFindings() (line 940) emits error findings on browser-export and worker-export routes when compositionGraph is absent but legacy shader facts exist in snapshot.shaders — this IS the authority ratchet in the planner, but there is NO dedicated test fixture proving it blocks legacy-only input in compositionGraphProjector.test.ts.
- EXPORTGUARD LEGACY FALLBACK: exportGuard.ts function hasTimelineShaderMetadata() (line 460) falls back to hasLegacyTimelineShaderStorage() via getTimelineClipShader()/getTimelinePostprocessShader() when no compositionGraph is provided. This is an intentional compatibility bridge, but it means the export guard itself CAN still read legacy storage — though only as a fallback when graph authority is absent, not as a competing authority. The allow-list explicitly documents this in timeline-domain.ts.
